<br>
Ideas perhaps could be:<br>
<br>
Runneyeye Citadel<br>
Befallen<br>
Crushbone<br>
Unrest<br>
Mistmoore pond/graveyard area<br>
Sarnak Fort in Lake of Ill Omen<br>
Goblin Caves in Lake of Ill Omen<br>
Derv camps<br>
Shadowed men camps<br>
Gorge of King Xorrb (Beholder)<br>
<br>
Camps could be:<br>
<br>
PBB's in Gorge of King Xorrb<br>
Savants Cap in Unrest<br>
CDS/PGT in Highhold<br>
Chitin Shell Armor/Chitin Shield in Upper Guk<br>
Various Sarnak items in Lake of Ill Omen<br>
Paw armor from outside Paw<br>
Dragoon Dirk in Crushbone<br>
<br>
Please post any other ideas.  Without your participation, nothing can happen. <p><font face="verdana,arial">-Giradella Broomrider (Benevolent Order)<br>
Magician of the 25th Season<br>
Prexus Server</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000044><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bbenevolentorder.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aislynn>Aislynn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/00 8:29:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fbenevolentordereventplanning.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eagle.cc.ukans.edu/~zmainz/face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Low level raids??</span><hr size=1> Mistmoore -- Sacremental dagger/crested helm/crested pauldrons/Mistmoore shield all can be held below lvl 30.<br>
<br>
Uguk -- Don't know the zone but there are TONS of camps that can be done.<br>
<br>
Runnyeye -- Staff of observers lens, BiBs, BI crown, BI medallion, BI Girdle., BI boots -- Some other stuff here but not exactly sure about them.<br>
<br>
Unrest -- Savants Cap/BS gloves, Thick Leather Apron/Opalline Earrings, BS mantle/tunic and DWB/jagged bands for the 30+ crowd.<br>
<br>
Najena -- Tentacle whip, Barbed leather whip, Large bronze armor, Ashenwood spear, FBR, Black Tome w/ Silvery runes, Dark Circlet (for crafted legs and not a bad item either for casters), Somekinda Armband that cleris and druids wear that is 3 str 3wis or something like that and Travelers Pack/bags (wt reducers)<br>
<br>
<br>
=D<br>
<br>
--Aislynn<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bbenevolentorder.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aislynn>Aislynn</A> at: 8/10/00 7:02:04 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000044><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bbenevolentorder.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aislynn>Aislynn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/10/00 7:06:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fbenevolentordereventplanning.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eagle.cc.ukans.edu/~zmainz/face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Low level raids??</span><hr size=1> Unrest and Najena are my favorites suggestions for this b/c There is stuff in each zone for people up to level 35, the experience isn't bad, and the common loots are exactly common and especially useful.  How many tanks still need an 8ac belt?  How many enchanters, bards, or trade skill people could use a 5 char earrings?  How many casters need FBR or the Black tome?  How many rangers or warriors could benefit from a 6/22 spear?  Also, Najena is VIRTUALLY empty all the time so I don't see the problem with going there and don't have to worry about it being taken.  If we start early enough on a weekend morning...unrest is empty too.<br>
<br>
Another idea is to raid Permafrost.  Unfortunately, my knowledge of PF is virtually nil.  I've been there like 3 times and don't really know the camps very well.  There is some nice loot to be gotten and experience FOR all levels.  Crystalline Blade, runed circlet, silver plated bracer, cold iron morning star, archy pack, silvery war axe, silvery 2hander--and I'm sure there is more.  If anyone knows this zone, I'm sure we can do this zone easily with 2 groups of lvl 25ishes and a supporting group of higher lvls.<br>
<br>
Just some suggestions.<br>
<br>
--Aislynn<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000044><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugiradella.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Giradella</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/10/00 12:51:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fbenevolentordereventplanning.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eagle.cc.ukans.edu/~stinnett/Girasmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Low level raids??</span><hr size=1> These all sound like pretty good ideas.  (I thought the silver plated bracer dropped in UGuk.  /e shrug)  Here are some level ranges that I know of as of today.  Forgive me if I'm off by a few.<br>
